{
  "abstract": "The geographical distribution of the major pests, Heliothis armigera, H. zea, and H. vlrescens,\r\nand the crop losses caused by these are reviewed. Although i t is generally considered that\r\nthe destruction of natural enemies by pesticide use and changes In cropping patterns and\r\nmanagement have promoted these insects to malor pest status, there are areas where H. armlgera\r\nIs a serious pest, although traditional agriculture is s t i l l practiced, and no pesticides\r\nare used. The dangers of a further increase in losses to Heliothis spp by breeding more\r\nsusceptible crops are described. There is a need for a more imaginative and holistic approach\r\nto research directed towards the management of these pests.",
